# {{lb|zh|[[controversial]]}} to be [[stranded]] [[ashore]]
#* {{zh-x|@鯈鯛 者，浮陽 之 魚 也，胠 於 沙 而 思 水，則 無 逮 矣。挂<!--sic--> 於 患 而 思 謹，則 無益 矣。|The mullet dart about near the surface of the water, but when they '''are stranded''' on the sand, though they may long for water, they will never reach it again. Similarly when it is already in the midst of calamity, though someone may wish he had been cautious, his wishing will be in vain.|CL|ref={{circa2|3<sup>rd</sup> {{BCE}}}},{{lw|zh|s:荀子/榮辱篇|荀子•榮辱|pref=《|suf=》}}<br>According to {{lw|zh|楊倞|tr=Yáng Jìng|t=fl. 819}}, here the character carries a similar meaning to {{l|zh|祛|t=to lose}}, while {{w|Yu Yue}} ({{lw|zh|俞樾}}, 1821~1907) reckoned it as a variant of {{l|zh|阹|t=to bar; to obstruct}}}}

